  "text": "institutes was gradually growing due to direct funding. This resulted in a positive trend in library subscription, one could see that more and more money was spent on scholarly resources. Annual surveys conducted by NEICON since 2006 indicated that e-resource acquisition budgets of leading universities increased by 10 times from 2006 to 2016. However, in 2014 due to economic crisis in Russia and almost a 100% drop in purchasing power of national currency, situation changed dramatically. The 2016 and 2017 surveys showed that research and educational institutions in Russia did not have enough money to maintain information support at appropriate level [CITATION_1] . In result, the number of resources subscribed with institution budgets shrunk by 38% and 80% in 2015 and 2016, respectively.",
